          "prompt_html": "<h1>NOTE COMPLETION 14</h1><p><strong>Questions 27 - 30</strong></p><p>Complete the notes.</p><p>Using <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND / OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p><p><strong>Jamie and Rebecca’s Presentation</strong></p><ul><li><p>Large countries currently shifting world economic balance of power:</p></li><li><p>China</p></li><li><p>Russia</p></li><li><p>India</p></li><li><p>Brazil</p></li><li><p>Reasons for shift: size of the populations, cheap labour and prices of <blank data-qid=\"q27\"/>.</p></li><li><p>Big growing demand for people knowing languages of above countries and for English <blank data-qid=\"q28\"/> and teaching.</p></li><li><p>China could be less important than <blank data-qid=\"q29\"/> in the future due to its population increase. English will probably remain important though.</p></li><li><p>Number of spoken languages between approx. 2,500 and <blank data-qid=\"q30\"/>. Hardly any of these studied by non native speakers.</p></li><li><p>English taught in most countries with structured education programme. This trend is getting stronger.</p></li></ul>",
